comment: Kanter (OKC) makes contact with Duncan's (SAS) body that affects his driving shot attempt but the foul is called on Adams (OKC).
Leonard (SAS) makes incidental contact with Waiters (OKC) on his legal move to the basket.
Leonard (SAS) maintains legal guarding position cleanly strips the ball from Waiters (OKC) prior to any incidental arm contact.
Green (SAS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Payne (OKC) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.

West (SAS) makes contact with Waiters's (OKC) arms during his driving shot attempt. Waiters has already gathered the ball when the foul occurs and takes a legal one, two step and is correctly awarded continuation.
West (SAS) sets the screen on Roberson (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Roberson (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Leonard's (SAS) drive and jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Marjanovic (SAS) sets the screen on Roberson (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Adams (OKC) and Marjanovic (SAS) briefly engage during rebounding, and the incidental contact as they transition upcourt causes Marjanovic to fall to the ground.
Waiters (OKC) makes incidental contact with Leonard (SAS) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Marjanovic (SAS) makes contact with Waiters's (OKC) arms that affects his driving shot attempt.
Roberson (OKC) cleanly blocks Duncan's (SAS) layup attempt.
Parker (SAS) makes incidental contact with Payne (OKC) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Green (SAS) stumbles prior to gaining possession of the ball and takes a legal step to establish his pivot foot.
Green (SAS) runs through the space of Payne (OKC) who sets a legal screen in the backcourt on the play.
